dc:description: Lamp fragment of reddish buff clay with reddish brown glaze.  Handle, large part of top and small part of base with adjoining side survive.  Broad plain rim, separated from discus by two grooves.  Discus decorated with stag running to the right.  Air hole at base of nozzle.  Ring handle with two grooves on upper circular groove.  Nozzle missing.
